softwareVersion.name: softwareVersion
softwareVersion.description: Version number of the storage management component of the systems management software.

globalStatus.name: globalStatus
globalStatus.description: Global health information for the subsystem managed by the Storage Management software. This global status is customized for HP OpenView. Other applications should refer to the agentSystemGlobalStatus entry in the globalData object group. Possible values: 1: Critical 2: Warning 3: Normal 4: Unknown

softwareManufacturer.name: softwareManufacturer
softwareManufacturer.description: Manufacturer information for the Storage Management software.

softwareProduct.name: softwareProduct
softwareProduct.description: Product information for the Storage Management software.

softwareDescription.name: softwareDescription
softwareDescription.description: Product Description for the Storage Management software.

displayName.name: displayName
displayName.description: Name of this management software for display purposes.

description.name: description
description.description: A short description of this management software.

agentVendor.name: agentVendor
agentVendor.description: The name of the management software manufacturer.

agentVersion.name: agentVersion
agentVersion.description: This entry is obsolete. Refer to softwareVersion.

agentSystemGlobalStatus.name: agentSystemGlobalStatus
agentSystemGlobalStatus.description: This entry is obsolete. Please use the value: agentGlobalSystemStatus. Note: Enumerated values have changed.

agentLastGlobalStatus.name: agentLastGlobalStatus
agentLastGlobalStatus.description: This entry is obsolete. Please use the value: agentLastGlobalSystemStatus. Note: Enumerated values have changed.

agentTimeStamp.name: agentTimeStamp
agentTimeStamp.description: The last time that the agent values have been updated. Universal time in sec since UTC 1/1/70.

agentGetTimeout.name: agentGetTimeout
agentGetTimeout.description: Suggested timeout value in milliseconds for how long the SNMP getter should wait while attempting to poll the SNMP agent.

agentModifiers.name: agentModifiers
agentModifiers.description: Agent functional modifiers, when set the modifier is active. Bit definitions: Bit 3: agent in debug mode. All other bits are product specific

agentRefreshRate.name: agentRefreshRate
agentRefreshRate.description: The rate, given in seconds, at which the cached data for SNMP is refreshed. The default value is 300 seconds, or 5 minutes.

agentHostname.name: agentHostname
agentHostname.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

agentIPAddress.name: agentIPAddress
agentIPAddress.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

agentSoftwareStatus.name: agentSoftwareStatus
agentSoftwareStatus.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

agentSnmpVersion.name: agentSnmpVersion
agentSnmpVersion.description: This entry is obsolete. Refer to softwareVersion.

agentMibVersion.name: agentMibVersion
agentMibVersion.description: Version of the Storage Management MIB.

agentManagementSoftwareURLName.name: agentManagementSoftwareURLName
agentManagementSoftwareURLName.description: The Universal Resource Locator (URL) of the systems management software.

agentGlobalSystemStatus.name: agentGlobalSystemStatus
agentGlobalSystemStatus.description: Global health information for the subsystem managed by the Storage Management software. This global status should be used by applications other than HP OpenView. HP OpenView should refer to the globalStatus in the root level object group. This is a rollup for the entire agent including any monitored devices. The status is intended to give initiative to a snmp monitor to get further data when this status is abnormal. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

agentLastGlobalSystemStatus.name: agentLastGlobalSystemStatus
agentLastGlobalSystemStatus.description: The previous global status of the system managed by the Storage Management software. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

agentSmartThermalShutdown.name: agentSmartThermalShutdown
agentSmartThermalShutdown.description: Indicates the status of smart thermal shutdown for PV220S and PV221S enclosures. Possible values: 1: Enabled 2: Disabled

channelTable.name: channelTable
channelTable.description: A table of controller channels. The number of entries is related to the number of channels supported by a RAID controller. Perc2 RAID controller supports a max of 4 channels per controller. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

channelEntry.name: channelEntry
channelEntry.description: An entry in the channel table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

channelNumber.name: channelNumber
channelNumber.description: Instance number of this channel entry.

channelName.name: channelName
channelName.description: The name of the channel as represented in Storage Management. The name will include the word channel and the instance. For example: Channel 1

channelState.name: channelState
channelState.description: The current condition of the channel. Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready - The I/O has resumed. 2: Failed 3: Online 4: Offline - The I/O has paused. 6: Degraded

channelSeverity.name: channelSeverity
channelSeverity.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management. It was replaced with RollUpStatus and ComponentStatus for each device.

channelTermination.name: channelTermination
channelTermination.description: The type of SCSI termination on this channel. Termination is required for proper operation of this channel. 1: Wide Termination (16 bit) 2: Narrow Termination (8 bit) 3: Not Terminated

channelSCSIID.name: channelSCSIID
channelSCSIID.description: The SCSI ID of the controller to which the channel belongs.

channelRollUpStatus.name: channelRollUpStatus
channelRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the channel state. This is the combined status of the channel and its components. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

channelComponentStatus.name: channelComponentStatus
channelComponentStatus.description: The status of the channel itself with out without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

channelNexusID.name: channelNexusID
channelNexusID.description: Durable unique ID for this channel.

channelDataRate.name: channelDataRate
channelDataRate.description: The data rate (SCSI speed) of the channel. Example: Ultra 320M SCSI

channelBusType.name: channelBusType
channelBusType.description: The bus type of the channel. Possible values: 1: SCSI 2: IDE 3: Fibre Channel 4: SSA 6: USB 7: SATA 8: SAS 9: PCIe

enclosureTable.name: enclosureTable
enclosureTable.description: A table of managed Enclosures. The number of entries is related to number of enclosures discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

enclosureEntry.name: enclosureEntry
enclosureEntry.description: An entry in the Enclosure table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

enclosureNumber.name: enclosureNumber
enclosureNumber.description: Instance number of the enclosure entry.

enclosureName.name: enclosureName
enclosureName.description: The enclosure's name as represented in Storage Management.

enclosureState.name: enclosureState
enclosureState.description: The current condition of the enclosure (which includes any devices connected to it.) Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready 2: Failed 3: Online 4: Offline 6: Degraded

enclosureSeverity.name: enclosureSeverity
enclosureSeverity.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management. It was replaced with RollUpStatus and ComponentStatus for each device.

enclosureID.name: enclosureID
enclosureID.description: Represents unique id for an enclosure.

enclosureProcessorVersion.name: enclosureProcessorVersion
enclosureProcessorVersion.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

enclosureServiceTag.name: enclosureServiceTag
enclosureServiceTag.description: Enclosure identification used when consulting customer support.

enclosureAssetTag.name: enclosureAssetTag
enclosureAssetTag.description: User definable asset tag for the enclosure.

enclosureAssetName.name: enclosureAssetName
enclosureAssetName.description: User definable asset name of the enclosure.

enclosureSplitBusPartNumber.name: enclosureSplitBusPartNumber
enclosureSplitBusPartNumber.description: The enclosure's split bus part number.

enclosureProductID.name: enclosureProductID
enclosureProductID.description: The enclosure's product identification. This also corresponds to the enclosure type.

enclosureKernelVersion.name: enclosureKernelVersion
enclosureKernelVersion.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management. Refer to enclosureFirmwareVersion for the firmware version of the enclosure.

enclosureESM1PartNumber.name: enclosureESM1PartNumber
enclosureESM1PartNumber.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

enclosureESM2PartNumber.name: enclosureESM2PartNumber
enclosureESM2PartNumber.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

enclosureType.name: enclosureType
enclosureType.description: The type of this enclosure. Possible values: 1: Internal 2: Dell PV200S (PV201S) 3: Dell PV210S (PV211S) 4: Dell PV220S (PV221S) 5: Dell PV660F 6: Dell PV224F 7: Dell PV660F / PV224F 8: Dell MD1000 9: Dell MD1120 10: Dell MD1200 11: Dell MD1220

enclosureProcessor2Version.name: enclosureProcessor2Version
enclosureProcessor2Version.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

enclosureConfig.name: enclosureConfig
enclosureConfig.description: The current configuration of the enclosure's backplane. Possible values: 1: Joined 2: Split Bus 3: Clustered 4: Unified

enclosureChannelNumber.name: enclosureChannelNumber
enclosureChannelNumber.description: The channel number, or bus, to which the enclosure is connected.

enclosureAlarm.name: enclosureAlarm
enclosureAlarm.description: The current status of the enclosure's alarm (PV220S, and PV221S only.) Possible values: 1: Disabled 2: Enabled

enclosureBackplanePartNumber.name: enclosureBackplanePartNumber
enclosureBackplanePartNumber.description: The part number of the enclosure's backplane.

enclosureSCSIID.name: enclosureSCSIID
enclosureSCSIID.description: The SCSI ID of the controller to which this enclosure is attached.

enclosureRollUpStatus.name: enclosureRollUpStatus
enclosureRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the enclosure state. This is the combined status of the enclosure and its components. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

enclosureComponentStatus.name: enclosureComponentStatus
enclosureComponentStatus.description: The status of the enclosure itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

enclosureNexusID.name: enclosureNexusID
enclosureNexusID.description: Durable unique ID for this enclosure.

enclosureFirmwareVersion.name: enclosureFirmwareVersion
enclosureFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware version of the enclosure.

enclosureSCSIRate.name: enclosureSCSIRate
enclosureSCSIRate.description: Actual SCSI rate in the enclosure.

enclosurePartNumber.name: enclosurePartNumber
enclosurePartNumber.description: The part number of the enclosure.

enclosureSASAddress.name: enclosureSASAddress
enclosureSASAddress.description: The specified SAS address if this is a SAS enclosure.

enclosureOccupiedSlotCount.name: enclosureOccupiedSlotCount
enclosureOccupiedSlotCount.description: Shows the number of physical disk slots occupied in a storage enclosure. Note: A value of 9999 indicates feature not available.

enclosureTotalSlots.name: enclosureTotalSlots
enclosureTotalSlots.description: Shows the total number of physical slots in a storage enclosure; it includes total count of occupied and empty slots. Note: A value of 9999 indicates feature not available.

enclosureEmptySlotCount.name: enclosureEmptySlotCount
enclosureEmptySlotCount.description: Shows the number of empty physical disk slots in a storage enclosure. Note: A value of 9999 indicates feature not available.

enclosureExpressServiceCode.name: enclosureExpressServiceCode
enclosureExpressServiceCode.description: Express Service Code (ESC) is base10 converted numerical value of service tag.

arrayDiskTable.name: arrayDiskTable
arrayDiskTable.description: A table of managed Array Disks. The number of entries is related to number of Array Disks discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

arrayDiskEntry.name: arrayDiskEntry
arrayDiskEntry.description: An entry in the Array Disk table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

arrayDiskNumber.name: arrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk entry.

arrayDiskName.name: arrayDiskName
arrayDiskName.description: The name of the array disk as represented in Storage Management.

arrayDiskState.name: arrayDiskState
arrayDiskState.description: The current condition of the array disk. Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready - Available for use, but no RAID configuration has been assigned. 2: Failed - Not operational. 3: Online - Operational. RAID configuration has been assigned. 4: Offline - The drive is not available to the RAID controller. 6: Degraded - Refers to a fault-tolerant array/virtual disk that has a failed disk. 7: Recovering - Refers to state of recovering from bad blocks on disks. 11: Removed - Indicates that array disk has been removed. 13: Non-RAID - Indicates that array disk is not a RAID capable disk 14: Not Ready - Applicable for PCIeSSD devices indicating that the device is in locked state 15: Resynching - Indicates one of the following types of disk operations: Transform Type, Reconfiguration, and Check Consistency. 22: Replacing - Indicates copyback operation is in progress. 23: Spinning Down - Transit state when the physical disk is spinning down for physical disk power management. 24: Rebuild 25: No Media - CD-ROM or removable disk has no media. 26: Formatting - In the process of formatting. 28: Diagnostics - Diagnostics are running. 34: Predictive failure 35: Initializing: Applies only to virtual disks on PERC, PERC 2/SC, and PERC 2/DC controllers. 39: Foreign 40: Clear 41: Unsupported 53: Incompatible 56: Read Only - Applicable for PCIeSSD devices. Indicates that device has reached read-only state

arrayDiskSeverity.name: arrayDiskSeverity
arrayDiskSeverity.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management. It was replaced with RollUpStatus and ComponentStatus for each device.

arrayDiskProductID.name: arrayDiskProductID
arrayDiskProductID.description: The model number of the array disk.

arrayDiskSerialNo.name: arrayDiskSerialNo
arrayDiskSerialNo.description: The array disk's unique identification number from the manufacturer.

arrayDiskRevision.name: arrayDiskRevision
arrayDiskRevision.description: The firmware version of the array disk.

arrayDiskEnclosureID.name: arrayDiskEnclosureID
arrayDiskEnclosureID.description: The SCSI ID of the enclosure processor to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskChannel.name: arrayDiskChannel
arrayDiskChannel.description: The bus to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskLengthInMB.name: arrayDiskLengthInMB
arrayDiskLengthInMB.description: The size in megabytes of the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskLengthInBytes.name: arrayDiskLengthInBytes
arrayDiskLengthInBytes.description: The size of the array disk in bytes that is less than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskLengthInMB is the total size of the array disk.

arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB
arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB.description: The size in megabytes of the largest contiguous free space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is less than a megabyte.

arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInByt.name: arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInByt.description: The size of the largest contiguous free space on this array disk in bytes that is less than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB is the total size of the largest contiguous free space on the array disk.

arrayDiskTargetID.name: arrayDiskTargetID
arrayDiskTargetID.description: The SCSI target ID which this array disk is assigned.

arrayDiskLunID.name: arrayDiskLunID
arrayDiskLunID.description: The array disk's logical unit number.

arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB
arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB.description: The amount in megabytes of the used space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes.name: arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes.description: The size in bytes of the used space on the array disk that is smaller than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB is the total amount of used space on the array disk.

arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB
arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB.description: The amount in megabytes of the free space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes.name: arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes.description: The size in bytes of the free space on the array disk that is smaller than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB is the total amount of free space on the array disk.

arrayDiskBusType.name: arrayDiskBusType
arrayDiskBusType.description: The bus type of the array disk. Possible values: 1: SCSI 2: IDE 3: Fibre Channel 4: SSA 6: USB 7: SATA 8: SAS 9: PCIe

arrayDiskSpareState.name: arrayDiskSpareState
arrayDiskSpareState.description: The status of the array disk as a spare. Possible states: 1 : disk is a member of a virtual disk 2 : disk is a member of a disk group 3 : disk is a global hot spare 4 : disk is a dedicated hot spare 5 : not a spare 99: not applicable

arrayDiskRollUpStatus.name: arrayDiskRollUpStatus
arrayDiskRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the array disk state. This is the combined status of the array disk and its components. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

arrayDiskComponentStatus.name: arrayDiskComponentStatus
arrayDiskComponentStatus.description: The status of the array disk itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

arrayDiskDeviceName.name: arrayDiskDeviceName
arrayDiskDeviceName.description: The operating system device name for this disk. This property is only applicable to array disks attached to a RAID controller.

arrayDiskNexusID.name: arrayDiskNexusID
arrayDiskNexusID.description: Durable unique ID for this array disk.

arrayDiskPartNumber.name: arrayDiskPartNumber
arrayDiskPartNumber.description: The part number of the disk.

arrayDiskSASAddress.name: arrayDiskSASAddress
arrayDiskSASAddress.description: The specified SAS address if this is a SAS disk.

arrayDiskNegotiatedSpeed.name: arrayDiskNegotiatedSpeed
arrayDiskNegotiatedSpeed.description: The speed at which the drive is actually running in MPS (megabytes per second).

arrayDiskCapableSpeed.name: arrayDiskCapableSpeed
arrayDiskCapableSpeed.description: The maximum speed at which the drive is capable of negotiating in MPS (megabytes per second).

arrayDiskSmartAlertIndication.name: arrayDiskSmartAlertIndication
arrayDiskSmartAlertIndication.description: Indicated whether the disk has received a predictive failure. Possible values: 1: No - disk has not received a predictive failure alert 2: Yes - disk has received a predictive failure alert

arrayDiskManufactureDay.name: arrayDiskManufactureDay
arrayDiskManufactureDay.description: The day of the week (1=Sunday thru 7=Saturday) on which this disk was manufactured.

arrayDiskManufactureWeek.name: arrayDiskManufactureWeek
arrayDiskManufactureWeek.description: The week (1 thru 53) in which this disk was manufactured.

arrayDiskManufactureYear.name: arrayDiskManufactureYear
arrayDiskManufactureYear.description: The four digit year in which this disk was manufactured.

arrayDiskMediaType.name: arrayDiskMediaType
arrayDiskMediaType.description: The Media type of the array disk. Possible Values: 1:unknown 2:hdd 3:ssd

arrayDiskDellCertified.name: arrayDiskDellCertified
arrayDiskDellCertified.description: Indicates if array disk is certified by Dell. Value: 1 - Certified, 0 - Not Certified, 99 - Unknown

arrayDiskAltaVendorId.name: arrayDiskAltaVendorId
arrayDiskAltaVendorId.description: Provides vendor information for Alta interposer.

arrayDiskAltaProductId.name: arrayDiskAltaProductId
arrayDiskAltaProductId.description: Provides product id for Alta interposer.

arrayDiskAltaRevisionId.name: arrayDiskAltaRevisionId
arrayDiskAltaRevisionId.description: Provides revision id for Alta interposer.

arrayDiskEncryptionCapable.name: arrayDiskEncryptionCapable
arrayDiskEncryptionCapable.description: Indicates if physical disk is Encryption capable. Value: 1 - Capable, 0 - Not Capable, 99 - Not Applicable

arrayDiskEncrypted.name: arrayDiskEncrypted
arrayDiskEncrypted.description: Indicates if the physical disk has encryption enabled. Value: 1 - Yes, 0 - No, 99 - Not Applicable

arrayDiskPowerState.name: arrayDiskPowerState
arrayDiskPowerState.description: Indicates power state of a physical drive. Value: 0 - Spun up, 1- Spun down, 255 - Transition, 99 - Not Applicable

arrayDiskDriveWriteCache.name: arrayDiskDriveWriteCache
arrayDiskDriveWriteCache.description: Indicates drive write cache capability for PCIe SSD devices. Value: 1 - Enabled, 0 - Disabled, 99 - Undetermined/Not Applicable

arrayDiskModelNumber.name: arrayDiskModelNumber
arrayDiskModelNumber.description: Provides PCIe SSD device model number.

arrayDiskLifeRemaining.name: arrayDiskLifeRemaining
arrayDiskLifeRemaining.description: Provides PCIe SSD device life remaining in percentage. Value: 0..100, 999 - Undetermined/Not Applicable

arrayDiskDriverVersion.name: arrayDiskDriverVersion
arrayDiskDriverVersion.description: Provides PCIe SSD device driver version.

arrayDiskDeviceLifeStatus.name: arrayDiskDeviceLifeStatus
arrayDiskDeviceLifeStatus.description: Provides PCIe SSD device life status. Possible Values: -1: Not Available / Not Applicable 1: Drive Health Good 2: Approaching Warranty Coverage Expiry 3: Warranty Coverage Expired 4: Approaching Read Only 5: Read Only

arrayDiskReadOnly.name: arrayDiskReadOnly
arrayDiskReadOnly.description: Provides PCIe SSD's Read Only attribute. Possible Values: Yes, No, Not Applicable

arrayDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance.name: arrayDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance
arrayDiskRemainingRatedWriteEndurance.description: Provides PCIe SSD device Remaining Rated Write Endurance Possible Values: 0-100% ,Not Available/Not Applicable

arrayDiskSectorSize.name: arrayDiskSectorSize
arrayDiskSectorSize.description: Provides the information regarding sector size of array disk. Possible values are: 512 or 4096.

arrayDiskPICapable.name: arrayDiskPICapable
arrayDiskPICapable.description: Provides the information regarding T10 PI capability of Array disk. Possible values are: 0 (T10 PI incapable) or 1 (T10 PI capable).

arrayDiskMaxLinkWidth.name: arrayDiskMaxLinkWidth
arrayDiskMaxLinkWidth.description: Provides the information regarding Max Link Width of Array disk. Possible values are: 0 - 8.

arrayDiskNegotiatedLinkWidth.name: arrayDiskNegotiatedLinkWidth
arrayDiskNegotiatedLinkWidth.description: Provides the information regarding Negtioated Link Width of Array disk. Possible values are: 0 - 8.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between array disks, their enclosure, and their associated controller. For each object in the table, its object number corresponds to an instance number in the appropriate MIB table for that object where all of the object properties can be found. Note: Only array disks that are part of an enclosure will be listed in this table. Backplanes are considered enclosures by Storage Management.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEntry.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEntry
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEntry.description: An entry in the Array Disk Enclosure Connection table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk connection entry. This table shows the array disk to enclosure relationship.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNam.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNam.description: The name of the array disk in this connection as represented in Storage Management.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNum.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNum.description: The instance number of the array disk in the arrayDiskTable in this connection.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNam.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNam.description: The name of the enclosure as represented in Storage Management to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNum.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNum.description: The instance number in the enclosureTable of the enclosure to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNa.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNa.description: The name of the controller as represented in Storage Management to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNu.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNu.description: The instance number in the controllerTable of the controller to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable
arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between array disks, their channel, and their associated controller. For each object in the table, its object number corresponds to an instance number in the appropriate MIB table for that object where all of the object properties can be found. Note: Only array disks that are NOT part of an enclosure will be listed in this table. Backplanes are considered enclosures by Storage Management.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionEntry.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionEntry
arrayDiskChannelConnectionEntry.description: An entry in the Array Disk Channel Connection table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk connection entry. This table shows the array disk to SCSI channel relationship. There is no enclosure service processor associated with these array disks.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName.description: The name of the array disk in this connection as represented in Storage Management.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumbe.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumbe.description: The instance number of the array disk in the arrayDiskTable in this connection.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName.description: The name of the channel as represented in Storage Management to which is array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber.description: The instance number of the channel in the channelTable to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName.description: The name of the controller as represented in Storage Management to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumb.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumb.description: The instance number in the controllerTable of the controller to which this array disk is connected.

fanTable.name: fanTable
fanTable.description: A table of managed Fans. The number of entries is related to number of Fans discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent. Note: The properties in this table may not be applicable to all entries.

fanEntry.name: fanEntry
fanEntry.description: An entry in the Fan table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

fanNumber.name: fanNumber
fanNumber.description: Instance number of this fan entry.

fanName.name: fanName
fanName.description: The fan's name as represented in Storage Management.

fanState.name: fanState
fanState.description: The current condition of the fan. Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready 2: Failed 3: Online 4: Offline 6: Degraded 21: Missing

fanSeverity.name: fanSeverity
fanSeverity.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management. It was replaced with RollUpStatus and ComponentStatus for each device.

fanProbeUnit.name: fanProbeUnit
fanProbeUnit.description: This entry is obsolete for Storage Management.

fanProbeMinWarning.name: fanProbeMinWarning
fanProbeMinWarning.description: This entry is obsolete. This setting is not supported by fans managed under Storage Management.

fanProbeMinCritical.name: fanProbeMinCritical
fanProbeMinCritical.description: This entry is obsolete. This setting is not supported by fans managed under Storage Management.

fanProbeMaxWarning.name: fanProbeMaxWarning
fanProbeMaxWarning.description: This entry is obsolete. This setting is not supported by fans managed under Storage Management.

fanProbeMaxCritical.name: fanProbeMaxCritical
fanProbeMaxCritical.description: This entry is obsolete. This setting is not supported by fans managed under Storage Management.

fanProbeCurrValue.name: fanProbeCurrValue
fanProbeCurrValue.description: The current speed of the fan.

fan1PartNumber.name: fan1PartNumber
fan1PartNumber.description: The part number of the fan in the enclosure.

fan2PartNumber.name: fan2PartNumber
fan2PartNumber.description: This entry is obsolete. This setting is not supported by fans managed under Storage Management.

fanRollUpStatus.name: fanRollUpStatus
fanRollUpStatus.description: Severity of the fan state. This is the combined status of the fan and its components. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

fanComponentStatus.name: fanComponentStatus
fanComponentStatus.description: The status of the fan itself without the propagation of any contained component status. Possible values: 1: Other 2: Unknown 3: OK 4: Non-critical 5: Critical 6: Non-recoverable

fanNexusID.name: fanNexusID
fanNexusID.description: Durable unique ID for this fan.

fanRevision.name: fanRevision
fanRevision.description: The revision number of the fan in the enclosure.

fanConnectionTable.name: fanConnectionTable
fanConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between each fan on the managed node and its enclosure. Each enclosure number in the table corresponds to that enclosure instance in the Enclosure Table.

fanConnectionEntry.name: fanConnectionEntry
fanConnectionEntry.description: An entry in the Fan Connection table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

fanConnectionNumber.name: fanConnectionNumber
fanConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this fan connection entry.

fanConnectionFanName.name: fanConnectionFanName
fanConnectionFanName.description: The name of the fan in this connection as represented in Storage Management.

fanConnectionFanNumber.name: fanConnectionFanNumber
fanConnectionFanNumber.description: The instance number of the fan in the fanTable in this connection.

fanConnectionEnclosureName.name: fanConnectionEnclosureName
fanConnectionEnclosureName.description: The name of the enclosure as represented in Storage Management to which this fan belongs.

fanConnectionEnclosureNumber.name: fanConnectionEnclosureNumber
